<p>To output a number as a string, simply call the <code>format()</code> function of the Y.Number class:</p>

```
YUI().use("datatype-number-format-advanced", function(Y) {
    alert(Y.Number.format(123123123, { style: "NUMBER_STYLE" }));
});
```

The `style` param can take the following values: CURRENCY_STYLE, ISO_CURRENCY_STYLE, NUMBER_STYLE, PERCENT_STYLE, PLURAL_CURRENCY_STYLE, SCIENTIFIC_STYLE.
This is helpful, for instance, when displaying numbers as currency:

```
YUI().use("datatype-number-format-advanced", function(Y) {
    alert(Y.Number.format(123123123.176,{
        style: "CURRENCY_STYLE"
    }));
});
```
